            "heading": "The honey behind the healing",
            "heading_size": "hxxl"
          }
        },
        "text_BHyzMg": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Mānuka honey is unlike any other.<br/><br/>Produced from the nectar of Leptospermum scoparium—a wildflower native to New Zealand—this rare honey is harvested during a short bloom that lasts just a few weeks each year. In that window, bees create something extraordinary: a honey rich in naturally occurring compounds like methylglyoxal (MGO), known for its powerful antibacterial properties.<br/><br/>At First Honey, we go even further. We source only high-potency Manuka from remote, pollution-free forests, then refine it using our proprietary ApiPure™ system-preserving its natural strength and purifying it to medical-grade standards.<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        }
