        },
        "text_pEdLUg": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>MGO, or methylglyoxal, is the antibacterial compound that gives Mānuka honey its unique power—and makes it so rare. It forms naturally in the nectar of the Mānuka flower and is transferred into the honey by bees, along with other bioactive compounds. The higher the MGO, the stronger the antibacterial activity.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
