            "heading": "Where it begins",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "text_CxVEXg": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The Mānuka forests of the Wairarapa region are at the heart of our honey. Their isolation, biodiversity, and untouched environment shape everything we do—and everything our honey becomes.<br/><br/>These forests sequester large amounts of carbon from the atmosphere, helping reduce the impact of climate change. We support this natural balance with ongoing planting programs and thousands of new Mānuka trees established so far.<br/><br/>We work in step with the seasons and follow practices that protect the health of the hives and the surrounding ecosystem. Every drop carries the purity of this place—and the care that began long before it reached your hands.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
